@node "arexxproject" " MUIEcon - ARexx: PROJECT-RELATED COMMANDS "
   @{b}NEW@{ub}
      DESCRIPTION
         NEW creates a new project and work area.  The investment/loan
         list is cleared.

      RETURNS
         none


   @{b}CLEAR@{ub} FORCE/S
      DESCRIPTION
         CLEAR clears the current project and its work area.
         The investment/loan list is cleared.  The FORCE option will
         bypass the @{"Modified Project Requester" link "glossary"}.

      RETURNS
         none


   @{b}OPEN@{ub} FILENAME, FORCE/S
      DESCRIPTION
         Opens the specified data file and reads it into the I/L list.
         If no FILENAME is specified, a file requester will prompt the
         user.  FORCE supresses the @{"Modified Project Requester" link "glossary"}.

      RETURNS
         none


   @{b}SAVE@{ub}
      DESCRIPTION
         Saves the current project to the current filename.  If the
         project is unnamed, a file requester will appear.

      RETURNS
         none


   @{b}SAVEAS@{ub} NAME
      DESCRIPTION
         Saves the current project under the NAME specified.  If no NAME
         is specified, a file requester will appear.
      RETURNS
         none


   @{b}PRINT@{ub} PROMPT/S ALL/S
      DESCRIPTION
         Prints the currently selected items to the printer.  Use the
         ALL option to print all data.  PROMPT will provide the system
         Printer Prefs tool to set printing parameters.  PROMPT and ALL
         are mutually exclusive.  That is, PRINT PROMPT ALL is invalid.

      RETURNS
         none


   @{b}CLOSE@{ub}
      DESCRIPTION
         CLOSE creates a new project and work area.  The investment/loan
         list is cleared.

      RETURNS
         none


   @{b}QUIT@{ub}
      DESCRIPTION
         QUIT exits the application.

      RETURNS
         none
@endnode

@node "arexxblock" " MUIEcon - ARexx: BLOCK-RELATED COMMANDS "

   MUIEcon Block Commands do NOT support the Amiga Clipboard.  The data
   is stored in a non-standard format that would be useless to
   Clipboard-aware programs.  To move data into and out of the I/L list,
   use the @{" APPLICATION-SPECIFIC COMMANDS " link "arexxmuiecon"}.


   @{b}CUT@{ub}
      DESCRIPTION
         CUT will delete the active item from the I/L list.

      RETURNS
         none


   @{b}COPY@{ub}
      DESCRIPTION
         COPY will make a copy of the active item in the I/L list.
         Note that only one item may be copied at a time.  So only the
         first selection of multiple selections will be copied.

      RETURNS
         none


   @{b}PASTE@{ub}
      DESCRIPTION
         PASTE will paste the currently copied or cut item into the
         I/L list.  If no data exists in the copy buffer, PASTE has
         no effect.

      RETURNS
         none


   @{b}ERASE@{ub} FORCE/S
      DESCRIPTION
         ERASE will delete the active item from the I/L list.
         The FORCE option will suppress the "Are you sure?" requester.

      RETURNS
         none
@endnode

@node "arexxwindow" " MUIEcon - ARexx: WINDOW-RELATED COMMANDS "
   @{b}MOVEWINDOW@{ub} WINDOW, LEFTEDGE/N, TOPEDGE/N
      DESCRIPTION
         WINDOW is either "MAIN" or "DENT" for the main window or the
            Data ENTry window.
         LEFTEDGE is the horizontal ( <- X -> ) coordinate.

                                    ^
                                    |
         TOPEDGE  is the vertical ( Y ) coordinate.
                                    |
                                    v



      RETURNS
         -1 = Couldn't move window to specified location.
          0 = OK


   @{b}SIZEWINDOW@{ub} WINDOW, WIDTH/N, HEIGHT/N
      DESCRIPTION
         WINDOW is either "MAIN" or "DENT" for the main window or the
            Data ENTry window.
         WIDTH and HEIGHT specify the width and height of the window
         in pixels.

      RETURNS
         -1 = Couldn't size window to specified limits.
          0 = OK


   @{b}CHANGEWINDOW@{ub} WINDOW, LEFTEDGE/N,TOPEDGE/N, WIDTH/N,HEIGHT/N
      DESCRIPTION
         CHANGEWINDOW performs a sizing and a move operation on the
         specified window in a single step for greater visual appeal.

         WINDOW is either "MAIN" or "DENT" for the main window or the
            Data ENTry window.

         LEFTEDGE is the horizontal ( <- X -> ) coordinate.

                                    ^
                                    |
         TOPEDGE  is the vertical ( Y ) coordinate.
                                    |
                                    v

         WIDTH and HEIGHT specify the width and height of the window
         in pixels.

      RETURNS
         -1 = Couldn't move or size window to specified limits.
          0 = OK


   @{b}WINDOWTOFRONT@{ub} WINDOW
      DESCRIPTION
         WINDOWTOFRONT brings the specified window to the front of all
         other windows.

         WINDOW is either "MAIN" or "DENT" for the main window or the
            Data ENTry window.

      RETURNS
         -1 = Specified window was not open and therefore couldn't
              bring to front.
          0 = OK


   @{b}WINDOWTOBACK@{ub} WINDOW
      DESCRIPTION
         WINDOWTOBACK pushes the specified window behind all other
         windows.

         WINDOW is either "MAIN" or "DENT" for the main window or the
            Data ENTry window.

      RETURNS
         -1 = Specified window was not open and therefore couldn't
              pushed to the back.
          0 = OK


   @{b}ACTIVATEWINDOW@{ub} WINDOW
      DESCRIPTION
         This command activates a the specified window.

         WINDOW is either "MAIN" or "DENT" for the main window or the
            Data ENTry window.

      RETURNS
         none


   @{b}ZOOMWINDOW@{ub} WINDOW
      DESCRIPTION
         This command zooms the specified window to its alternate size.

         WINDOW is either "MAIN" or "DENT" for the main window or the
            Data ENTry window.

      RETURNS
         none


   @{b}UNZOOMWINDOW@{ub} WINDOW
      DESCRIPTION
         This command restores a zoomed window to its original size.

         WINDOW is either "MAIN" or "DENT" for the main window or the
            Data ENTry window.

      RETURNS
         none
@endnode

@node "arexxmuiecon" " MUIEcon - ARexx: APPLICATION-SPECIFIC COMMANDS "
   @{b}SORTBY@{ub} SORTTYPE
      DESCRIPTION
         SORTBY toggles the sorting type of the I/L List.
         SORTTYPE must be either "NAME" or "ENTRYTYPE".

      RETURNS
         none


   @{b}SETACTIVELINE@{ub} NONE/S, LINE/N
      DESCRIPTION
         Sets the active line to the line you specify.  If NONE is
         specified, all lines are made inactive.  Valid values for LINE
         are 1 through the number of items in the list.  The first line
         is 1 (not zero).

      RETURNS
         none


   @{b}SELECT@{ub} LINE/N
      DESCRIPTION
         Selects the specified LINE in the I/L List.  Valid values for
         LINE are 1 through the number of items in the list.  The first
         line is 1 (not zero).

      RETURNS
         none


   @{b}DESELECT@{ub} LINE/N
      DESCRIPTION
         De-selects the specified LINE in the I/L List.  Valid values for
         LINE are 1 through the number of items in the list.  The first
         line is 1 (not zero).

      RETURNS
         none


   @{b}QUERYITEM@{ub} SELECTED/S, LINE/N, DELIMETER
      DESCRIPTION
         Queries the specified LINE if SELECTED is not specified.
         Searches for the first selected after or including the specified
         LINE if SELECTED is specified.  Valid values for LINE are 1
         through the number of items in the list.  The first line is 1
         (not zero).

      RETURNS
         Returns a string of parameters separated by a one char delimeter
         specified in DELIMETER option.  The default delimeter is the
         backslash character ('\\').  The order of the items in the return
         string is:
            NAME
            ENTRY-TYPE
            RESULT
            VALUE1
            VALUE2
            VALUE3
            VALUE4
            VALUE5

         See the discussion in the @{b}Investment/Loan List@{ub} section of
         the @{" Main Window " link "mainwdw"} section for more details on this format.


   @{b}QUERYNUMITEMS@{ub}
      DESCRIPTION

      RETURNS
         Returns the number of items in the I/L List.


   @{b}I1INVFVINV@{ub}
      NAME/A, VAL1/A, VAL2/A, VAL3/A, VAL4/A, NOREQ/S, CONTCOMP/S

      VALUES entered from left to right should be:
         ·  Initial Investment
         ·  APR
         ·  Periods Per Year
         ·  Number of Years

      If any values are omitted or are illegal, an error requester will
      appear unless you use the NOREQ option.  The CONTCOMP option
      calculates using continuous compounding.


   @{b}I2INVFVREGDEP@{ub}
      NAME/A, VAL1/A, VAL2/A, VAL3/A, VAL4/A, NOREQ/S, CONTCOMP/S

      VALUES entered from left to right should be:
         ·  Amount of Reg Deposit
         ·  APR
         ·  Deposits Per Year
         ·  Number of Years

      If any values are omitted or are illegal, an error requester will
      appear unless you use the NOREQ option.  The CONTCOMP option
      calculates using continuous compounding.


   @{b}I3INVFVDESIRED@{ub}
      NAME/A, VAL1/A, VAL2/A, VAL3/A, VAL4/A, NOREQ/S, CONTCOMP/S

      VALUES entered from left to right should be:
